3450/*
3451 * Perform some tests on expressions which can't be done in build() and
3452 * functions called by build(). These tests must be done here because
3453 * we need some information about the context in which the operations
3454 * are performed.
3455 * After all tests are performed, expr() frees the memory which is used
3456 * for the expression.
3457 */
3458void
3459expr(tnode_t *tn, int vctx, int tctx, int dofreeblk)
3460{
3461
3462 if (tn == NULL && nerr == 0)
3463 LERROR("expr()");
3464
3465 if (tn == NULL) {
3466 tfreeblk();
3467 return;
3468 }
3469
3470 /* expr() is also called in global initialisations */
3471 if (dcs->d_ctx != EXTERN)
3472 chkreach();
3473
3474 chkmisc(tn, vctx, tctx, !tctx, 0, 0, 0);
3475 if (tn->tn_op == ASSIGN) {
3476 if (hflag && tctx)
3477 /* assignment in conditional context */
3478 warning(159);
3479 } else if (tn->tn_op == CON) {
3480 if (hflag && tctx && !ccflg)
3481 /* constant in conditional context */
3482 warning(161);
3483 }
3484 if (!modtab[tn->tn_op].m_sideeff) {
3485 /*
3486 * for left operands of COMMA this warning is already
3487 * printed
3488 */
3489 if (tn->tn_op != COMMA && !vctx && !tctx)
3490 nulleff(tn);
3491 }
3492 if (dflag)
3493 displexpr(tn, 0);
3494
3495 /* free the tree memory */
3496 if (dofreeblk)
3497 tfreeblk();
3498}
3499
3500static void
3501nulleff(tnode_t *tn)
3502{
3503
3504 if (!hflag)
3505 return;
3506
3507 while (!modtab[tn->tn_op].m_sideeff) {
3508 if (tn->tn_op == CVT && tn->tn_type->t_tspec == VOID) {
3509 tn = tn->tn_left;
3510 } else if (tn->tn_op == LOGAND || tn->tn_op == LOGOR) {
3511 /*
3512 * && and || have a side effect if the right operand
3513 * has a side effect.
3514 */
3515 tn = tn->tn_right;
3516 } else if (tn->tn_op == QUEST) {
3517 /*
3518 * ? has a side effect if at least one of its right
3519 * operands has a side effect
3520 */
3521 tn = tn->tn_right;
3522 } else if (tn->tn_op == COLON || tn->tn_op == COMMA) {
3523 /*
3524 * : has a side effect if at least one of its operands
3525 * has a side effect
3526 */
3527 if (modtab[tn->tn_left->tn_op].m_sideeff) {
3528 tn = tn->tn_left;
3529 } else if (modtab[tn->tn_right->tn_op].m_sideeff) {
3530 tn = tn->tn_right;
3531 } else {
3532 break;
3533 }
3534 } else {
3535 break;
3536 }
3537 }
3538 if (!modtab[tn->tn_op].m_sideeff)
3539 /* expression has null effect */
3540 warning(129);
3541}

3543/*
3544 * Dump an expression to stdout
3545 * only used for debugging
3546 */
3547static void
3548displexpr(tnode_t *tn, int offs)
3549{
3550 uint64_t uq;
3551
3552 if (tn == NULL) {
3553 (void)printf("%*s%s\n", offs, "", "NULL");
3554 return;
3555 }
3556 (void)printf("%*sop %s ", offs, "", modtab[tn->tn_op].m_name);
3557
3558 if (tn->tn_op == NAME) {
3559 (void)printf("%s: %s ",
3560 tn->tn_sym->s_name, scltoa(tn->tn_sym->s_scl));
3561 } else if (tn->tn_op == CON && isftyp(tn->tn_type->t_tspec)) {
3562 (void)printf("%#g ", (double)tn->tn_val->v_ldbl);
3563 } else if (tn->tn_op == CON && isityp(tn->tn_type->t_tspec)) {
3564 uq = tn->tn_val->v_quad;
3565 (void)printf("0x %08lx %08lx ", (long)(uq >> 32) & 0xffffffffl,
3566 (long)uq & 0xffffffffl);
3567 } else if (tn->tn_op == CON) {
3568 if (tn->tn_type->t_tspec != PTR)
3569 LERROR("displexpr()");
3570 (void)printf("0x%0*lx ", (int)(sizeof (void *) * CHAR_BIT / 4),
3571 (u_long)tn->tn_val->v_quad);
3572 } else if (tn->tn_op == STRING) {
3573 if (tn->tn_strg->st_tspec == CHAR) {
3574 (void)printf("\"%s\"", tn->tn_strg->st_cp);
3575 } else {
3576 char *s;
3577 size_t n;
3578 n = MB_CUR_MAX * (tn->tn_strg->st_len + 1);
3579 s = xmalloc(n);
3580 (void)wcstombs(s, tn->tn_strg->st_wcp, n);
3581 (void)printf("L\"%s\"", s);
3582 free(s);
3583 }
3584 (void)printf(" ");
3585 } else if (tn->tn_op == FSEL) {
3586 (void)printf("o=%d, l=%d ", tn->tn_type->t_foffs,
3587 tn->tn_type->t_flen);
3588 }
3589 (void)printf("%s\n", ttos(tn->tn_type));
3590 if (tn->tn_op == NAME || tn->tn_op == CON || tn->tn_op == STRING)
3591 return;
3592 displexpr(tn->tn_left, offs + 2);
3593 if (modtab[tn->tn_op].m_binary ||
3594 (tn->tn_op == PUSH && tn->tn_right != NULL)) {
3595 displexpr(tn->tn_right, offs + 2);
3596 }
3597}

3599/*
3600 * Called by expr() to recursively perform some tests.
3601 */
3602/* ARGSUSED */
3603void
3604chkmisc(tnode_t *tn, int vctx, int tctx, int eqwarn, int fcall, int rvdisc,
3605 int szof)
3606{
3607 tnode_t *ln, *rn;
3608 mod_t *mp;
3609 int nrvdisc, cvctx, ctctx;
3610 op_t op;
3611 scl_t sc;
3612 dinfo_t *di;
3613
3614 if (tn == NULL)
3615 return;
3616
3617 ln = tn->tn_left;
3618 rn = tn->tn_right;
3619 mp = &modtab[op = tn->tn_op];
3620
3621 switch (op) {
3622 case AMPER:
3623 if (ln->tn_op == NAME && (reached || rchflg)) {
3624 if (!szof)
3625 setsflg(ln->tn_sym);
3626 setuflg(ln->tn_sym, fcall, szof);
3627 }
3628 if (ln->tn_op == STAR && ln->tn_left->tn_op == PLUS)
3629 /* check the range of array indices */
3630 chkaidx(ln->tn_left, 1);
3631 break;
3632 case LOAD:
3633 if (ln->tn_op == STAR && ln->tn_left->tn_op == PLUS)
3634 /* check the range of array indices */
3635 chkaidx(ln->tn_left, 0);
3636 /* FALLTHROUGH */
3637 case PUSH:
3638 case INCBEF:
3639 case DECBEF:
3640 case INCAFT:
3641 case DECAFT:
3642 case ADDASS:
3643 case SUBASS:
3644 case MULASS:
3645 case DIVASS:
3646 case MODASS:
3647 case ANDASS:
3648 case ORASS:
3649 case XORASS:
3650 case SHLASS:
3651 case SHRASS:
3652 case REAL:
3653 case IMAG:
3654 if (ln->tn_op == NAME && (reached || rchflg)) {
3655 sc = ln->tn_sym->s_scl;
3656 /*
3657 * Look if there was a asm statement in one of the
3658 * compound statements we are in. If not, we don't
3659 * print a warning.
3660 */
3661 for (di = dcs; di != NULL; di = di->d_nxt) {
3662 if (di->d_asm)
3663 break;
3664 }
3665 if (sc != EXTERN && sc != STATIC &&
3666 !ln->tn_sym->s_set && !szof && di == NULL) {
3667 /* %s may be used before set */
3668 warning(158, ln->tn_sym->s_name);
3669 setsflg(ln->tn_sym);
3670 }
3671 setuflg(ln->tn_sym, 0, 0);
3672 }
3673 break;
3674 case ASSIGN:
3675 if (ln->tn_op == NAME && !szof && (reached || rchflg)) {
3676 setsflg(ln->tn_sym);
3677 if (ln->tn_sym->s_scl == EXTERN)
3678 outusg(ln->tn_sym);
3679 }
3680 if (ln->tn_op == STAR && ln->tn_left->tn_op == PLUS)
3681 /* check the range of array indices */
3682 chkaidx(ln->tn_left, 0);
3683 break;
3684 case CALL:
3685 if (ln->tn_op != AMPER || ln->tn_left->tn_op != NAME)
3686 LERROR("chkmisc(op=%s != %s || %s != %s)",
3687 getopname(ln->tn_op), getopname(AMPER),
3688 getopname(ln->tn_left->tn_op), getopname(NAME));
3689 if (!szof)
3690 outcall(tn, vctx || tctx, rvdisc);
3691 break;
3692 case EQ:
3693 /* equality operator "==" found where "=" was exp. */
3694 if (hflag && eqwarn)
3695 warning(160);
3696 break;
3697 case CON:
3698 case NAME:
3699 case STRING:
3700 return;
3701 /* LINTED206: (enumeration values not handled in switch) */
3702 case OR:
3703 case XOR:
3704 case NE:
3705 case GE:
3706 case GT:
3707 case LE:
3708 case LT:
3709 case SHR:
3710 case SHL:
3711 case MINUS:
3712 case PLUS:
3713 case MOD:
3714 case DIV:
3715 case MULT:
3716 case STAR:
3717 case UMINUS:
3718 case UPLUS:
3719 case DEC:
3720 case INC:
3721 case COMPL:
3722 case NOT:
3723 case POINT:
3724 case ARROW:
3725 case NOOP:
3726 case AND:
3727 case FARG:
3728 case CASE:
3729 case INIT:
3730 case RETURN:
3731 case ICALL:
3732 case CVT:
3733 case COMMA:
3734 case FSEL:
3735 case COLON:
3736 case QUEST:
3737 case LOGOR:
3738 case LOGAND:
3739 break;
3740 }
3741
3742 cvctx = mp->m_vctx;
3743 ctctx = mp->m_tctx;
3744 /*
3745 * values of operands of ':' are not used if the type of at least
3746 * one of the operands (for gcc compatibility) is void
3747 * XXX test/value context of QUEST should probably be used as
3748 * context for both operands of COLON
3749 */
3750 if (op == COLON && tn->tn_type->t_tspec == VOID)
3751 cvctx = ctctx = 0;
3752 nrvdisc = op == CVT && tn->tn_type->t_tspec == VOID;
3753 chkmisc(ln, cvctx, ctctx, mp->m_eqwarn, op == CALL, nrvdisc, szof);
3754
3755 switch (op) {
3756 case PUSH:
3757 if (rn != NULL)
3758 chkmisc(rn, 0, 0, mp->m_eqwarn, 0, 0, szof);
3759 break;
3760 case LOGAND:
3761 case LOGOR:
3762 chkmisc(rn, 0, 1, mp->m_eqwarn, 0, 0, szof);
3763 break;
3764 case COLON:
3765 chkmisc(rn, cvctx, ctctx, mp->m_eqwarn, 0, 0, szof);
3766 break;
3767 case COMMA:
3768 chkmisc(rn, vctx, tctx, mp->m_eqwarn, 0, 0, szof);
3769 break;
3770 default:
3771 if (mp->m_binary)
3772 chkmisc(rn, 1, 0, mp->m_eqwarn, 0, 0, szof);
3773 break;
3774 }
3775
3776}

3778/*
3779 * Checks the range of array indices, if possible.
3780 * amper is set if only the address of the element is used. This
3781 * means that the index is allowd to refere to the first element
3782 * after the array.
3783 */
3784static void
3785chkaidx(tnode_t *tn, int amper)
3786{
3787 int dim;
3788 tnode_t *ln, *rn;
3789 int elsz;
3790 int64_t con;
3791
3792 ln = tn->tn_left;
3793 rn = tn->tn_right;
3794
3795 /* We can only check constant indices. */
3796 if (rn->tn_op != CON)
3797 return;
3798
3799 /* Return if the left node does not stem from an array. */
3800 if (ln->tn_op != AMPER)
3801 return;
3802 if (ln->tn_left->tn_op != STRING && ln->tn_left->tn_op != NAME)
3803 return;
3804 if (ln->tn_left->tn_type->t_tspec != ARRAY)
3805 return;
3806
3807 /*
3808 * For incomplete array types, we can print a warning only if
3809 * the index is negative.
3810 */
3811 if (incompl(ln->tn_left->tn_type) && rn->tn_val->v_quad >= 0)
3812 return;
3813
3814 /* Get the size of one array element */
3815 if ((elsz = length(ln->tn_type->t_subt, NULL)) == 0)
3816 return;
3817 elsz /= CHAR_BIT;
3818
3819 /* Change the unit of the index from bytes to element size. */
3820 if (isutyp(rn->tn_type->t_tspec)) {
3821 con = (uint64_t)rn->tn_val->v_quad / elsz;
3822 } else {
3823 con = rn->tn_val->v_quad / elsz;
3824 }
3825
3826 dim = ln->tn_left->tn_type->t_dim + (amper ? 1 : 0);
3827
3828 if (!isutyp(rn->tn_type->t_tspec) && con < 0) {
3829 /* array subscript cannot be negative: %ld */
3830 warning(167, (long)con);
3831 } else if (dim > 0 && (uint64_t)con >= (uint64_t)dim) {
3832 /* array subscript cannot be > %d: %ld */
3833 warning(168, dim - 1, (long)con);
3834 }
3835}

3837/*
3838 * Check for ordered comparisons of unsigned values with 0.
3839 */
3840static void
3841chkcomp(op_t op, tnode_t *ln, tnode_t *rn)
3842{
3843 char buf[64];
3844 tspec_t lt, rt;
3845 mod_t *mp;
3846
3847 lt = ln->tn_type->t_tspec;
3848 rt = rn->tn_type->t_tspec;
3849 mp = &modtab[op];
3850
3851 if (ln->tn_op != CON && rn->tn_op != CON)
3852 return;
3853
3854 if (!isityp(lt) || !isityp(rt))
3855 return;
3856
3857 if ((hflag || pflag) && lt == CHAR && rn->tn_op == CON &&
3858 (rn->tn_val->v_quad < 0 ||
3859 rn->tn_val->v_quad > (int)~(~0U << (CHAR_BIT - 1)))) {
3860 /* nonportable character comparison, op %s */
3861 warning(230, mp->m_name);
3862 return;
3863 }
3864 if ((hflag || pflag) && rt == CHAR && ln->tn_op == CON &&
3865 (ln->tn_val->v_quad < 0 ||
3866 ln->tn_val->v_quad > (int)~(~0U << (CHAR_BIT - 1)))) {
3867 /* nonportable character comparison, op %s */
3868 warning(230, mp->m_name);
3869 return;
3870 }
3871 if (isutyp(lt) && !isutyp(rt) &&
3872 rn->tn_op == CON && rn->tn_val->v_quad <= 0) {
3873 if (rn->tn_val->v_quad < 0) {
3874 /* comparison of %s with %s, op %s */
3875 warning(162, tyname(buf, sizeof(buf), ln->tn_type),
3876 "negative constant", mp->m_name);
3877 } else if (op == LT || op == GE || (hflag && op == LE)) {
3878 /* comparison of %s with %s, op %s */
3879 warning(162, tyname(buf, sizeof(buf), ln->tn_type),
3880 "0", mp->m_name);
3881 }
3882 return;
3883 }
3884 if (isutyp(rt) && !isutyp(lt) &&
3885 ln->tn_op == CON && ln->tn_val->v_quad <= 0) {
3886 if (ln->tn_val->v_quad < 0) {
3887 /* comparison of %s with %s, op %s */
3888 warning(162, "negative constant",
3889 tyname(buf, sizeof(buf), rn->tn_type), mp->m_name);
3890 } else if (op == GT || op == LE || (hflag && op == GE)) {
3891 /* comparison of %s with %s, op %s */
3892 warning(162, "0", tyname(buf, sizeof(buf), rn->tn_type),
3893 mp->m_name);
3894 }
3895 return;
3896 }
3897}

3899/*
3900 * Takes an expression an returns 0 if this expression can be used
3901 * for static initialisation, otherwise -1.
3902 *
3903 * Constant initialisation expressions must be constant or an address
3904 * of a static object with an optional offset. In the first case,
3905 * the result is returned in *offsp. In the second case, the static
3906 * object is returned in *symp and the offset in *offsp.
3907 *
3908 * The expression can consist of PLUS, MINUS, AMPER, NAME, STRING and
3909 * CON. Type conversions are allowed if they do not change binary
3910 * representation (including width).
3911 */
3912int
3913conaddr(tnode_t *tn, sym_t **symp, ptrdiff_t *offsp)
3914{
3915 sym_t *sym;
3916 ptrdiff_t offs1, offs2;
3917 tspec_t t, ot;
3918
3919 switch (tn->tn_op) {
3920 case MINUS:
3921 if (tn->tn_right->tn_op == CVT)
3922 return conaddr(tn->tn_right, symp, offsp);
3923 else if (tn->tn_right->tn_op != CON)
3924 return (-1);
3925 /* FALLTHROUGH */
3926 case PLUS:
3927 offs1 = offs2 = 0;
3928 if (tn->tn_left->tn_op == CON) {
3929 offs1 = (ptrdiff_t)tn->tn_left->tn_val->v_quad;
3930 if (conaddr(tn->tn_right, &sym, &offs2) == -1)
3931 return (-1);
3932 } else if (tn->tn_right->tn_op == CON) {
3933 offs2 = (ptrdiff_t)tn->tn_right->tn_val->v_quad;
3934 if (tn->tn_op == MINUS)
3935 offs2 = -offs2;
3936 if (conaddr(tn->tn_left, &sym, &offs1) == -1)
3937 return (-1);
3938 } else {
3939 return (-1);
3940 }
3941 *symp = sym;
3942 *offsp = offs1 + offs2;
3943 break;
3944 case AMPER:
3945 if (tn->tn_left->tn_op == NAME) {
3946 *symp = tn->tn_left->tn_sym;
3947 *offsp = 0;
3948 } else if (tn->tn_left->tn_op == STRING) {
3949 /*
3950 * If this would be the front end of a compiler we
3951 * would return a label instead of 0.
3952 */
3953 *offsp = 0;
3954 }
3955 break;
3956 case CVT:
3957 t = tn->tn_type->t_tspec;
3958 ot = tn->tn_left->tn_type->t_tspec;
3959 if ((!isityp(t) && t != PTR) || (!isityp(ot) && ot != PTR))
3960 return (-1);
3961#ifdef notdef
3962 /*
3963 * consider:
3964 * struct foo {
3965 * unsigned char a;
3966 * } f = {
3967 * (u_char)(u_long)(&(((struct foo *)0)->a))
3968 * };
3969 * since psize(u_long) != psize(u_char) this fails.
3970 */
3971 else if (psize(t) != psize(ot))
3972 return (-1);
3973#endif
3974 if (conaddr(tn->tn_left, symp, offsp) == -1)
3975 return (-1);
3976 break;
3977 default:
3978 return (-1);
3979 }
3980 return (0);
3981}

3983/*
3984 * Concatenate two string constants.
3985 */
3986strg_t *
3987catstrg(strg_t *strg1, strg_t *strg2)
3988{
3989 size_t len1, len2, len;
3990
3991 if (strg1->st_tspec != strg2->st_tspec) {
3992 /* cannot concatenate wide and regular string literals */
3993 error(292);
3994 return (strg1);
3995 }
3996
3997 len1 = strg1->st_len;
3998 len2 = strg2->st_len + 1; /* + NUL */
3999 len = len1 + len2;
4000
4001#define COPY(F) \
4002 do { \
4003 strg1->F = xrealloc(strg1->F, len * sizeof(*strg1->F)); \
4004 (void)memcpy(strg1->F + len1, strg2->F, len2 * sizeof(*strg1->F)); \
4005 free(strg2->F); \
4006 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
4007
4008 if (strg1->st_tspec == CHAR)
4009 COPY(st_cp);
4010 else
4011 COPY(st_wcp);
4012
4013 strg1->st_len = len - 1; /* - NUL */;
4014 free(strg2);
4015
4016 return (strg1);
4017}

4019/*
4020 * Print a warning if the given node has operands which should be
4021 * parenthesized.
4022 *
4023 * XXX Does not work if an operand is a constant expression. Constant
4024 * expressions are already folded.
4025 */
4026static void
4027precconf(tnode_t *tn)
4028{
4029 tnode_t *ln, *rn;
4030 op_t lop, rop = NOOP;
4031 int lparn, rparn = 0;
4032 mod_t *mp;
4033 int dowarn;
4034
4035 if (!hflag)
4036 return;
4037
4038 mp = &modtab[tn->tn_op];
4039
4040 lparn = 0;
4041 for (ln = tn->tn_left; ln->tn_op == CVT; ln = ln->tn_left)
4042 lparn |= ln->tn_parn;
4043 lparn |= ln->tn_parn;
4044 lop = ln->tn_op;
4045
4046 if (mp->m_binary) {
4047 rparn = 0;
4048 for (rn = tn->tn_right; tn->tn_op == CVT; rn = rn->tn_left)
4049 rparn |= rn->tn_parn;
4050 rparn |= rn->tn_parn;
4051 rop = rn->tn_op;
4052 }
4053
4054 dowarn = 0;
4055
4056 switch (tn->tn_op) {
4057 case SHL:
4058 case SHR:
4059 if (!lparn && (lop == PLUS || lop == MINUS)) {
4060 dowarn = 1;
4061 } else if (!rparn && (rop == PLUS || rop == MINUS)) {
4062 dowarn = 1;
4063 }
4064 break;
4065 case LOGOR:
4066 if (!lparn && lop == LOGAND) {
4067 dowarn = 1;
4068 } else if (!rparn && rop == LOGAND) {
4069 dowarn = 1;
4070 }
4071 break;
4072 case AND:
4073 case XOR:
4074 case OR:
4075 if (!lparn && lop != tn->tn_op) {
4076 if (lop == PLUS || lop == MINUS) {
4077 dowarn = 1;
4078 } else if (lop == AND || lop == XOR) {
4079 dowarn = 1;
4080 }
4081 }
4082 if (!dowarn && !rparn && rop != tn->tn_op) {
4083 if (rop == PLUS || rop == MINUS) {
4084 dowarn = 1;
4085 } else if (rop == AND || rop == XOR) {
4086 dowarn = 1;
4087 }
4088 }
4089 break;
4090 /* LINTED206: (enumeration values not handled in switch) */
4091 case DECAFT:
4092 case XORASS:
4093 case SHLASS:
4094 case NOOP:
4095 case ARROW:
4096 case ORASS:
4097 case POINT:
4098 case NAME:
4099 case NOT:
4100 case COMPL:
4101 case CON:
4102 case INC:
4103 case STRING:
4104 case DEC:
4105 case INCBEF:
4106 case DECBEF:
4107 case INCAFT:
4108 case FSEL:
4109 case CALL:
4110 case COMMA:
4111 case CVT:
4112 case ICALL:
4113 case LOAD:
4114 case PUSH:
4115 case RETURN:
4116 case INIT:
4117 case CASE:
4118 case FARG:
4119 case SUBASS:
4120 case ADDASS:
4121 case MODASS:
4122 case DIVASS:
4123 case MULASS:
4124 case ASSIGN:
4125 case COLON:
4126 case QUEST:
4127 case LOGAND:
4128 case NE:
4129 case EQ:
4130 case GE:
4131 case GT:
4132 case LE:
4133 case LT:
4134 case MINUS:
4135 case PLUS:
4136 case MOD:
4137 case DIV:
4138 case MULT:
4139 case AMPER:
4140 case STAR:
4141 case UMINUS:
4142 case SHRASS:
4143 case UPLUS:
4144 case ANDASS:
4145 case REAL:
4146 case IMAG:
4147 break;
4148 }
4149
4150 if (dowarn) {
4151 /* precedence confusion possible: parenthesize! */
4152 warning(169);
4153 }
